If that's true, the last line in the convexhull can be removed. So inside the while loop, we should remove the last elements of _convexhull and _x. So the code inside the while loop should be:
_convexhull. RemoveAt(_convexhull. Count - 1);
_x.RemoveAt(_x. Count - 1);

That way, we maintain the convex hull correctly by removing the redundant lines. Otherwise, the convex hull wouldn't be built properly, leading to incorrect query results.
